  "prompt": "What are the best books of all time?",
  "response": "The concept of \"best books of all time\" can be subjective, as it often depends on personal taste, cultural background, and specific interests. However, some works are frequently mentioned in literary discussions for their impact, storytelling, and artistry. Here are some highly regarded titles across various genres and periods:\n\n### Classic Literature\n1. **\"Pride and Prejudice\"** by Jane Austen\n2. **\"Moby-Dick\"** by Herman Melville\n3. **\"War and Peace\"** by Leo Tolstoy\n4. **\"Crime and Punishment\"** by Fyodor Dostoevsky\n5. **\"To Kill a Mockingbird\"** by Harper Lee\n\n### Modern Classics\n6. **\"1984\"** by George Orwell\n7. **\"The Great Gatsby\"** by F. Scott Fitzgerald\n8. **\"One Hundred Years of Solitude\"** by Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez\n9. **\"The Catcher in the Rye\"** by J.D. Salinger\n10. **\"Beloved\"** by Toni Morrison\n\n### Science Fiction & Fantasy\n11. **\"Dune\"** by Frank Herbert\n12. **\"The Lord of the Rings\"** by J.R.R. Tolkien\n13. **\"Fahrenheit 451\"** by Ray Bradbury\n14. **\"Neuromancer\"** by William Gibson\n15. **\"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\"** by Douglas Adams\n\n### Non-Fiction\n16. **\"Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind\"** by Yuval Noah Harari\n17. **\"The Diary of a Young Girl\"** by Anne Frank\n18. **\"Guns, Germs, and Steel\"** by Jared Diamond\n19. **\"Educated\"** by Tara Westover\n20. **\"The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks\"** by Rebecca Skloot\n\n### Poetry\n21. **\"The Complete Poems\"** by Emily Dickinson\n22. **\"Leaves of Grass\"** by Walt Whitman\n23. **\"The Waste Land\"** by T.S. Eliot\n24. **\"The Collected Poems of W.B. Yeats\"** by W.B. Yeats\n25. **\"Milk and Honey\"** by Rupi Kaur\n\nThis list is not exhaustive and reflects a mix of styles, themes, and eras. Each of these works has left a mark on literature and continues to resonate with readers around the world.",
